He called again for the death penalty to be reinstated so that he can hang 20 criminals a day. 
 
“I will see to it that they are sentenced to the maximum,” he said of the policemen. “You give that power to me back again, I will execute them… I’ll hang them in one day, 20 of them – 20 a day.” he warned. 
 
Capital punishment has been a priority for Duterte, whose allies introduced a death penalty bill in Congress on June 30 last year, the same day as his inauguration. 
 
Meanwhile, a Senate investigation into Jee’s killing began on Thursday. 
 
Additional reporting by Reuters. 
 
